Description: Limestone fragment: this fragment in the shape of a rounded knob has the prenomen and nomen of Ramses III deeply incised on its face. This piece is composed of two separate fragments which entered the collection at different times and have been joined together. Part of the left edge is still lacking. The polished surface has worn thin on the base of the object and on the right edge of the face. Traces of inlay whose colour has now faded can be seen in certain hieroglyphs.
Curator's comments: Bibliography: E. A. Wallis Budge 'A Guide to the Fourth, Fifth and Sixth Egyptian Rooms, and the Coptic Room' (London, 1922), 271 (no. 122).
